<p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/05/Flag_of_Brazil.svg/43px-Flag_of_Brazil.svg.png"> Jos√© Aldo da Silva Oliveira Junior (born September 9, 1986) is a Brazilian mixed martial artist, who competes as a Featherweight in the Ultimate Fighting Championship. Aldo was the fourth and final WEC Featherweight Champion and thus, became the first and also is the current UFC Featherweight Champion during the UFC/WEC merger. He was named Sherdog's 2009 Fighter of the Year. As of August 10, 2015 he is #1 in official UFC pound-for-pound rankings and ranked the #1 Featherweight in the world by Sherdog. In the ten years from November 26, 2005 until November 26, 2015, Aldo never lost an MMA fight, thus marking an entire decade of invincibility, with 5 years ruling as a world champion (18 fights, 10 title fights, 9 title defenses).</p>